1
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:11,420
- Ah, so close!
- Bang!

2
00:00:11,420 --> 00:00:13,300
Alright, next!

3
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:14,800
Ahh!

4
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:17,120
No, no, no.
You do it like this.

5
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:19,180
- Bang!
- Whoa!

6
00:00:19,180 --> 00:00:21,260
I really wanna hit the piano.

7
00:00:21,260 --> 00:00:22,920
Okay, here goes!

8
00:00:22,920 --> 00:00:25,180
- What’re you doing?
- Oh...

9
00:00:25,180 --> 00:00:28,400
You scared me.
Oh, it’s Haryu.

10
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:32,000
We’re testing who can destroy
Donoko’s work, so stay out of it.

11
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,780
- Got a problem with that?
- Let me join too.

12
00:00:35,780 --> 00:00:37,260
Huh?

13
00:00:38,180 --> 00:00:40,920
I wanna be part of the group too.

14
00:00:40,920 --> 00:00:42,300
Huh?

15
00:00:50,420 --> 00:00:51,820
H-hey!

16
00:00:57,340 --> 00:00:58,800
Whoa...

17
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:03,040
You’re a samurai!

18
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:04,060
Ah.

19
00:01:09,320 --> 00:01:11,840
A samurai’s gotta have a chonmage.

20
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:14,360
- Right?
- Chonmage...

21
00:01:14,360 --> 00:01:16,320
Hey, the teacher's coming!

22
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:18,700
This is bad, bad!

23
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:20,700
Ah, Chonmage!

24
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,500
Ah... ah!

25
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:33,080
You’re terrible, Chonmage!

26
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:34,920
- You don’t stand a chance.
- Sorry.

27
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:36,800
You’re really bad at this.

28
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:21,280
THE RIGHT TO JUDGE

29
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:41,820
Next target is... Haryu.

30
00:03:42,780 --> 00:03:44,080
Haryu?

31
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:50,680
Ah, Chonmage!
Chonmage, right!

32
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:53,800
Um... if you're joking around,
please leave.

33
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:56,500
I'm not messing around,
I'm trying to remember!

34
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:58,980
Right?
Huh? Ah...

35
00:04:00,460 --> 00:04:02,800
A samurai, huh...

36
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:09,400
Stabbing, you think?

37
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:14,440
If it’s a stabbing, he could be
attacked anytime, anywhere.

38
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:15,840
Yeah...

39
00:04:16,820 --> 00:04:18,440
Damn...

40
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:26,960
Hey, isn’t he kinda a weird kid?

41
00:04:26,960 --> 00:04:30,660
He used to collect
cicada shells in his desk.

42
00:04:30,660 --> 00:04:34,420
- That was Kantaro.
- He hatched mantis eggs...

43
00:04:34,420 --> 00:04:36,820
Enough with that.

44
00:04:36,820 --> 00:04:42,800
Can you try to remember something meaningful,
like an address or contact info?

45
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,980
You were close, right?

46
00:04:44,980 --> 00:04:48,720
- He wasn’t at the reunion, right?
- Yeah.

47
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:54,020
Guess we have to follow someone
who knows many classmates…

48
00:04:54,020 --> 00:04:55,220
Ah.

49
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:59,100
Haryu? Yeah, I know it.

50
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:02,420
Ah, really? That helps.

51
00:05:02,420 --> 00:05:05,060
Our moms were close.

52
00:05:05,060 --> 00:05:07,800
Well, things turned out like that…

53
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:14,160
- What do you mean "like that"?
- Last year, his mom passed away.

54
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:17,980
You know, he also lost
his dad when he was little.

55
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:22,060
So my mom’s worried
he’s all alone now.

56
00:05:22,060 --> 00:05:26,300
She was being nosy and asked
for his address. I’ll send it to you.

57
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:28,300
Thanks. That helps.

58
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:33,300
No, but why Haryu all of a sudden?

59
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:42,300
Ah… well… I’ll tell you about it later.

60
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:45,800
Okay, got it.

61
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:48,300
Alright, see you then.

62
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:08,000
“Toward the Future.”

63
00:06:14,340 --> 00:06:16,100
See you.

64
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:31,220
“We’re going to Haryu’s place on Saturday.”

65
00:06:31,220 --> 00:06:33,040
“Bra-ger that!”

66
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:41,020
Why are you so annoyed?

67
00:06:41,020 --> 00:06:44,660
Why do guys turn so stupid
when they get together?

68
00:06:44,660 --> 00:06:46,800
- Here!
- Oh.

69
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,120
Ah...

70
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:54,480
Even if the taxi doesn’t move
or I step on gum, I don’t get frustrated.

71
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:56,280
What’s that?

72
00:06:57,920 --> 00:07:00,800
Did something happen?

73
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:03,300
No, nothing.

74
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:09,640
Um... If you want, I’m here to listen
anytime. Rely on me whenever.

75
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:12,780
Thanks.

76
00:07:18,420 --> 00:07:20,800
I’m starting to get annoyed.

77
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:30,300
Sorry about that.

78
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:48,080
- Is this the place?
- Looks like it.

79
00:07:58,120 --> 00:08:00,000
Chonmage?

80
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:04,300
Are you there, Chonmage?

81
00:08:07,460 --> 00:08:10,540
Hey, Chonmage!

82
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:14,120
Should we come back later?

83
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:31,800
Chonmage?

84
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:35,220
Hey, Chonmage.

85
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:41,720
Long time no see.

86
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:51,280
Hey, Chonmage.
It’s King. Takaki.

87
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:54,700
And I’m Koyama... Tabo.

88
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,380
Yo.

89
00:08:56,380 --> 00:08:58,020
King...?

90
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:01,720
Tabo...

91
00:09:04,260 --> 00:09:06,200
So it’s Donoko, huh...?

92
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:09,220
Long time no see.

93
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:14,220
So, it’s my turn...?

94
00:09:17,020 --> 00:09:20,400
- We’re here to talk…
- Come in.

95
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:23,040
Huh...?

96
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:25,720
Uh...

97
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,900
It’s a mess though.

98
00:09:34,340 --> 00:09:36,580
Ah... no worries.

99
00:09:36,580 --> 00:09:39,520
This is pretty normal
for a guy living alone.

100
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:46,000
Chonmage, you haven’t changed at all!

101
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:49,220
- Right?
- Yeah...

102
00:09:49,220 --> 00:09:51,980
- Like what?
- Huh?

103
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,960
Things have changed
since back then.

104
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:57,420
Everything.

105
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:12,120
Chonmage, um...
What are you doing now?

106
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:14,640
- Isn’t it obvious?
- Huh?

107
00:10:16,060 --> 00:10:17,820
I’m a total shut-in.

108
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,140
I see...

109
00:10:22,260 --> 00:10:26,660
And Tabo? You’re the CEO, right?

110
00:10:26,660 --> 00:10:28,700
That’s amazing.

111
00:10:28,700 --> 00:10:33,660
King got married...
Are you a dad now?

112
00:10:33,660 --> 00:10:37,720
- Yeah...
- Wow, that’s amazing...

113
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:42,660
And here I am, such a loser.

114
00:10:42,660 --> 00:10:45,420
No, that’s not true.

115
00:10:45,420 --> 00:10:48,240
Don’t worry about it.

116
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:50,420
I know that myself.

117
00:11:01,340 --> 00:11:02,900
Chonmage.

118
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,220
Here.

119
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:19,120
We came here to talk today...

120
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:21,720
- I know.
- Huh?

121
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:26,640
I never thought King and Tabo
would be here together.

122
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:28,640
Ah, the PC.

123
00:11:28,640 --> 00:11:30,560
- PC.
- Huh?

124
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:37,100
“Man plunges to his death from apartment”

125
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:38,420
This is…

126
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:46,260
- You know about the case...
- Of course I do.

127
00:11:46,260 --> 00:11:48,900
- Because this...
- H-hey, w-w-wait...

128
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:50,980
It's Donoko’s revenge, right?

129
00:11:52,620 --> 00:11:57,220
"What, now?" I thought,
but well, it can’t be helped.

130
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:04,080
- Can’t be helped?
- Yeah, of course!

131
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:07,720
We were the ones who bullied you.

132
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:28,720
Don’t hold back, it’s okay.

133
00:12:31,420 --> 00:12:35,720
See? I’m completely useless.

134
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:43,080
I’d be much happier if at least
I could be used for revenge.

135
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:46,220
Chonmage, calm down.

136
00:12:48,220 --> 00:12:51,300
We actually came to protect you.

137
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:53,840
- Protect?
- Yeah...

138
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:58,440
Like you said,
six of us are being targeted.

139
00:12:58,440 --> 00:13:03,960
But the culprit isn’t her.
It’s someone else.

140
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:09,100
We still don’t know who it is,
but I was attacked too.

141
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:13,720
But they protected me,
so I’m still here now.

142
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:17,220
- So if friends protect each other...
- I don’t care.

143
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:22,220
Friends...!

144
00:13:22,220 --> 00:13:23,720
No, we’re not.

145
00:13:25,220 --> 00:13:28,720
Everything has changed since back then.

146
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:41,220
Right now, I can’t do a thing,
can’t help anyone, I’m useless...

147
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:47,220
I don’t deserve to be your friend.

148
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,960
Once you’re done, leave.

149
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:55,720
- But...
- Get out!!

150
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:05,900
What’s his deal?
We’re worried about him!

151
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:10,300
Um... Did something
happen with Haryu?

152
00:14:10,300 --> 00:14:12,720
Hmm… something happen?

153
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:17,060
What should we do?

154
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:22,340
How should I know?!

155
00:14:22,340 --> 00:14:27,560
Even if we want to protect him,
there’s nothing we can do if he wants to die.

156
00:14:27,560 --> 00:14:29,220
Damn...

157
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:42,720
Damn it!!

158
00:15:01,980 --> 00:15:05,460
No, I’m tossing this one away.
Next, it’s my turn.

159
00:15:05,460 --> 00:15:09,640
He said we weren’t friends,
but I even included him in the song.

160
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:11,220
Yeah...

161
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:16,460
Maybe we weren’t friends
or anything to Chonmage.

162
00:15:17,740 --> 00:15:20,740
- Boss... Boss!
- Yeah?

163
00:15:20,740 --> 00:15:23,500
Isn’t she Sonoko Saruhashi?

164
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,320
Sonoko Saruhashi...

165
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:27,980
...Who’s that?

166
00:15:27,980 --> 00:15:31,940
You don’t know?
She’s a way too beautiful reporter!

167
00:15:31,940 --> 00:15:34,160
Huh? Like a celebrity or something?

168
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:37,480
- Something like that.
- Ah, I totally don’t get it.

169
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:42,540
Sorry, my celebrity knowledge
ended back in the Heisei era.

170
00:15:42,540 --> 00:15:44,820
It’s like the auditions on 'ASAYAN'.

171
00:15:44,820 --> 00:15:46,640
- I totally get that!
- Eh!

172
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:49,560
I never thought she was a
classmate of Takaki.

173
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:54,940
He said he can’t do
anything for anyone.

174
00:15:54,940 --> 00:15:56,980
What does that mean?

175
00:15:59,580 --> 00:16:01,460
Well, it’s like...

176
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:02,980
Alright!

177
00:16:02,980 --> 00:16:04,980
Black Magician, summon!

178
00:16:04,980 --> 00:16:12,920
While Kantaro and I played Yu-Gi-Oh!,
Nico read manga and Hin and Tabo gamed…

179
00:16:12,920 --> 00:16:16,480
Chonmage copied homework
for all of us.

180
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:22,960
I think that’s probably what he meant.

181
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,980
He was smart.

182
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:31,480
Maybe it’s no wonder
he didn’t think of us as friends.

183
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:35,800
You’re wrong, King.

184
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:39,820
I was the one playing Yu-Gi-Oh!.

185
00:16:39,820 --> 00:16:41,640
Huh?

186
00:16:41,640 --> 00:16:43,640
That’s the worst!

187
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:51,480
You and I played Yu-Gi-Oh!,
Nico read manga, Kantaro and Hin gamed.

188
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:55,840
So Chonmage was... doing homework.

189
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:58,720
Kantaro loved games,
so that had to be it.

190
00:16:58,720 --> 00:17:04,480
That doesn’t matter now, but either way,
it doesn’t change that we were using Chonmage.

191
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:07,000
- No, that’s not true.
- Huh?

192
00:17:08,180 --> 00:17:11,520
Chonmage played games too
after finishing homework.

193
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:13,600
The four of us played matches.

194
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:17,100
He was stupidly bad at Bomberman.

195
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:18,880
Four people?

196
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:20,980
Huh?

197
00:17:20,980 --> 00:17:28,980
Well, me and you were playing Yu-Gi-Oh!,
and Nico was reading manga alone...

198
00:17:33,460 --> 00:17:37,980
That makes four others...
Aren’t there seven of us?

199
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:42,260
- Who’s the other one?
- Huh...?

200
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:47,440
That’s how memories are.

201
00:17:48,860 --> 00:17:55,480
In the end, you only remember the
convenient parts and quickly forget the bad ones.

202
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:59,320
No, rather,
you try not to remember them.

203
00:18:01,180 --> 00:18:03,940
But the past doesn’t change.

204
00:18:03,940 --> 00:18:07,920
Even if you don’t try to recall it,
it’s always there.

205
00:18:09,780 --> 00:18:13,980
So, you have to face it properly.

206
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:19,980
Sorry, I was talking to myself
a bit too loudly.

207
00:18:24,740 --> 00:18:27,980
- Master, another one please.
- Okay, just a moment.

208
00:18:27,980 --> 00:18:30,420
Here you go!
Double flash, bang!

209
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:34,640
I wonder if he wasn’t having fun...

210
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:36,980
One more time!
Let’s play one more time...

211
00:18:36,980 --> 00:18:39,980
My Double Flash...!

212
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:59,880
What’s that? Did you draw it?

213
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:04,620
Ah... When we were in
elementary school. Scary, right?

214
00:19:04,620 --> 00:19:09,140
- That’s so messed up.
- Right.

215
00:19:09,140 --> 00:19:13,780
But at least you can laugh
when you see that drawing now.

216
00:19:13,780 --> 00:19:16,880
I can’t imagine that from you now.

217
00:19:20,580 --> 00:19:22,720
Can I see it too?

218
00:19:25,120 --> 00:19:26,180
Huh?

219
00:19:27,320 --> 00:19:29,900
Can I see it? Um…

220
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:39,400
CEO.

221
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:42,980
The police came by earlier to talk.

222
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:48,480
- They confirmed at 2 p.m.
- Understood.

223
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:52,560
Ah... I see.

224
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:55,000
Good to know you can move.

225
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:58,620
If it's a wheelchair, I’m
allowed to move around.

226
00:19:58,620 --> 00:20:02,900
It hurts, but the doctor said
he’d come explain later.

227
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:06,680
Ah... That doesn’t matter.

228
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:10,060
Forcus on the new place,
make it even better.

229
00:20:10,060 --> 00:20:11,880
Think of it as a chance.

230
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:14,100
Yeah, I guess.

231
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:17,740
"Yeah, I guess"...
That’s kinda cold.

232
00:20:19,060 --> 00:20:20,680
Are you here to visit?

233
00:20:25,360 --> 00:20:28,900
By the way, help me with the
interior design, will you?

234
00:20:28,900 --> 00:20:32,260
Yeah, leave it to me. I’ll help.

235
00:20:32,260 --> 00:20:34,300
That’s great.

236
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:36,320
You’re working, right?

237
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:38,880
Sorry to bother you. See you.

238
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:41,800
Yeah, see you.

239
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:42,980
Ugh... ouch.

240
00:20:42,980 --> 00:20:46,200
- Are you okay? I’ll get it.
- Ah, sorry...

241
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:51,480
- You look happy.
- Ah... yeah, I guess.

242
00:20:58,480 --> 00:21:00,480
Alright.

243
00:21:09,940 --> 00:21:14,440
Mr. Sakurai, I’m going to
take your blood pressure.

244
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:16,440
Mr. Sakurai?

245
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:18,440
Mr. Sakurai…!

246
00:21:35,380 --> 00:21:38,940
- Oh, Sir, hello.
- Ah, hello.

247
00:22:01,580 --> 00:22:04,300
"Messege: Kantaro."

248
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:06,060
That wheelchair is definitely
the one Mr. Sakurai was using.

249
00:23:06,060 --> 00:23:09,940
But Mr. Sakurai’s cellphone
hasn’t been found yet...

250
00:23:10,740 --> 00:23:12,080
Hey.

251
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:15,160
Sorry...

252
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:28,100
Welcome back.

253
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:31,940
Why did I forget to
buy the fukujinzuke...

254
00:23:33,720 --> 00:23:35,520
Hey, are you okay?

255
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:40,340
What’s wrong?

256
00:23:43,340 --> 00:23:46,380
Oh... I’ll go buy the fukujinzuke.

257
00:24:18,100 --> 00:24:21,760
I’m on the early shift,
so I’ll go to bed first.

258
00:24:21,760 --> 00:24:23,640
Good night.

259
00:24:48,580 --> 00:24:50,720
One thing I realized is...

260
00:24:52,500 --> 00:24:55,440
This won't end until they die.

261
00:24:56,720 --> 00:25:01,440
Besides, they’re no longer
choosing their methods.

262
00:25:02,420 --> 00:25:06,940
You’d better not do
anything rackless either...

263
00:25:06,940 --> 00:25:09,940
Seems like that.

264
00:25:09,940 --> 00:25:12,460
Haryu is in danger.

265
00:25:12,460 --> 00:25:15,640
He doesn’t fully
understand the situation.

266
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:20,400
We’ve got to hurry.
King, what should we do?

267
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:24,020
Hey, what are we gonna do, King?

268
00:25:26,700 --> 00:25:28,700
I don’t know...

269
00:25:28,700 --> 00:25:30,120
Huh?

270
00:25:31,620 --> 00:25:33,880
Don’t ask me...

271
00:25:35,420 --> 00:25:37,600
What’s that supposed to mean.

272
00:25:39,260 --> 00:25:42,440
Why are you asking me?

273
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:45,740
I don’t know what to do either.

274
00:25:47,660 --> 00:25:52,800
I want to do something too,
but I can’t protect anything.

275
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:57,000
I can’t do a thing.

276
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:01,300
So what then?

277
00:26:01,300 --> 00:26:05,060
- Wait for everyone to get killed?
- I’m telling you, I don’t know.

278
00:26:05,060 --> 00:26:09,740
You’re a dad!
You have a family, right?

279
00:26:09,740 --> 00:26:12,540
It’s not just your life alone!

280
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:23,700
Hey... that’s the same for everyone.

281
00:26:25,300 --> 00:26:31,680
Hin, Nico, Kantaro,
we’re all the same!

282
00:26:33,860 --> 00:26:44,200
Kantaro said he’d work hard to open
another shop and wanted me and you to come.

283
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:46,500
Why the hell!

284
00:26:50,280 --> 00:26:54,560
Why the hell do they have to die?
They were doing their best.

285
00:26:56,940 --> 00:26:58,980
I don’t get it anymore...

286
00:27:01,120 --> 00:27:03,180
Don’t mess with me...

287
00:27:14,860 --> 00:27:18,440
- Where are you going?
- To Haryu’s place.

288
00:27:18,440 --> 00:27:22,380
- Then we’ll go too...
- I really don’t think…

289
00:27:22,380 --> 00:27:25,760
you can convince Haryu now.

290
00:27:31,140 --> 00:27:33,160
I’m fine.

291
00:27:40,740 --> 00:27:44,940
“Burned Body Found in Abandoned Building
Identified as Male Restaurant Owner”

292
00:28:06,700 --> 00:28:08,560
Good.

293
00:28:08,560 --> 00:28:12,000
There’s just one favor I want to ask.

294
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:14,260
Huh? What?

295
00:28:14,260 --> 00:28:16,280
Could you open the door?

296
00:28:18,700 --> 00:28:22,960
- Just you alone?
- Yes, I’m alone today.

297
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:30,800
Excuse me.

298
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:35,940
Alright...

299
00:29:01,980 --> 00:29:04,420
So, you’re going to kill me after all...?

300
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:16,300
Huh?

301
00:29:16,300 --> 00:29:17,920
Excuse me.

302
00:29:30,080 --> 00:29:32,200
What are you doing?

303
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:36,200
You can tell, right? Cleaning.

304
00:29:36,200 --> 00:29:37,960
Why?

305
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:40,200
Doesn’t matter.

306
00:29:54,100 --> 00:29:55,620
Is this...?

307
00:29:57,260 --> 00:30:00,860
Yes, what does it look like to you?

308
00:30:00,860 --> 00:30:02,100
Huh?

309
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:06,860
I made my dream come true.

310
00:30:12,180 --> 00:30:14,620
“Our dreams”

311
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:33,200
Alright, it’s done!

312
00:31:16,400 --> 00:31:20,700
Then I put it into the time capsule.

313
00:31:24,920 --> 00:31:28,540
It definitely wouldn’t turn out like this.

314
00:31:28,540 --> 00:31:30,700
I swore that.

315
00:31:33,480 --> 00:31:38,020
I worked hard.

316
00:31:40,460 --> 00:31:45,800
No matter how tough it got,
I didn’t blame others.

317
00:31:45,800 --> 00:31:50,280
I made real effort to change myself.

318
00:31:54,700 --> 00:31:57,400
I’m sorry!

319
00:31:57,400 --> 00:32:01,700
Really... I’m really sorry!

320
00:32:03,700 --> 00:32:05,020
I...

321
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:10,400
I used you...

322
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:18,340
I was gloomy, unathletic, and jealous...

323
00:32:18,340 --> 00:32:20,540
Let me join too.

324
00:32:20,540 --> 00:32:22,200
Huh?

325
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:24,480
I want to be part of the group too.

326
00:32:24,480 --> 00:32:26,700
That’s why…

327
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:34,200
I knew it was a terrible thing to do...

328
00:32:36,240 --> 00:32:37,700
But...

329
00:32:37,700 --> 00:32:41,080
- Here we go.
- Okay.

330
00:32:41,080 --> 00:32:44,400
Huh?
Whose backpack is this?

331
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:46,560
- Give it back.
- Here.

332
00:32:54,800 --> 00:32:57,340
Chonmage, pass.

333
00:32:57,340 --> 00:32:58,960
I...

334
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:03,580
Throw it!

335
00:33:03,580 --> 00:33:06,200
I couldn’t do anything about it...

336
00:33:10,220 --> 00:33:16,700
I thought if I didn’t bully you,
I couldn’t stay friends with them.

337
00:33:16,700 --> 00:33:20,200
Chonmage!
Where are you throwing that!

338
00:33:20,200 --> 00:33:21,840
Let’s go home.

339
00:33:28,700 --> 00:33:33,700
I’m really... really sorry.

340
00:33:44,780 --> 00:33:48,920
I cleaned the bathroom
but use mold prevention quarterly

341
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:52,700
and change the dehumidifier biannually.

342
00:34:00,580 --> 00:34:01,980
Alright.

343
00:34:36,700 --> 00:34:38,180
What…?

344
00:34:40,240 --> 00:34:45,280
Even if you apologize,
you haven’t changed in my eyes.

345
00:34:47,500 --> 00:34:53,700
Who else but yourself can
truly change you?

346
00:34:56,460 --> 00:34:59,200
You have to change yourself.

347
00:35:02,040 --> 00:35:07,700
I was able to do it...
so can you, right?

348
00:36:31,800 --> 00:36:34,700
“Wait for me at IMAKUNI.”

349
00:37:07,160 --> 00:37:08,820
I finished.

350
00:37:12,060 --> 00:37:15,680
Hurry, hurry!

351
00:37:15,680 --> 00:37:18,700
Wait!

352
00:37:19,780 --> 00:37:21,700
Shall we go?

353
00:37:32,260 --> 00:37:34,760
- I can’t take it.
- Huh? What...?

354
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:37,080
- I’ll sing.
- No, no... wait a minute...

355
00:37:38,700 --> 00:37:40,880
- Welcome!
- Welcome!

356
00:37:41,660 --> 00:37:44,260
Sorry I’m late.

357
00:37:46,460 --> 00:37:48,260
Chonmage...

358
00:37:54,260 --> 00:37:56,260
I’m sorry!

359
00:37:59,200 --> 00:38:03,720
The other day...
I was actually really happy...

360
00:38:05,320 --> 00:38:08,760
You two remembered me...

361
00:38:08,760 --> 00:38:11,760
You thought of me as a friend...

362
00:38:13,680 --> 00:38:17,260
But I didn’t have any confidence...

363
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:24,760
All this time... since then...

364
00:38:31,340 --> 00:38:33,260
So...

365
00:38:35,520 --> 00:38:37,760
My mom died...

366
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:45,020
Hin… Nico... Kantaro too...

367
00:38:46,620 --> 00:38:52,380
If I’m going to lose everything…
I’d rather it never existed at all…

368
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:55,740
But...

369
00:39:04,760 --> 00:39:06,760
That…

370
00:39:09,760 --> 00:39:12,260
Because it was fun.

371
00:39:19,140 --> 00:39:27,540
King and Tabo were popular, like you lived in a
different world from someone like me.

372
00:39:27,540 --> 00:39:29,760
But still, you two...

373
00:39:31,540 --> 00:39:34,260
Hey, Chonmage.

374
00:39:34,260 --> 00:39:36,260
Do you wanna play?

375
00:39:36,260 --> 00:39:40,260
You even played with someone like me.

376
00:39:46,760 --> 00:39:48,520
You’re terrible, Chonmage!

377
00:39:48,520 --> 00:39:50,560
- You don’t stand a chance.
- Sorry.

378
00:39:50,560 --> 00:39:52,760
You’re really bad at this.

379
00:39:52,760 --> 00:39:55,560
Ah, then let’s change the game.

380
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:58,760
It’s only because you’re bad
that we have no choice.

381
00:40:03,280 --> 00:40:06,320
- Here, I’ll lend this to you.
- Huh?

382
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:08,760
Practice by the next time.

383
00:40:11,260 --> 00:40:14,760
I really did have fun...

384
00:40:16,260 --> 00:40:17,680
So...

385
00:40:19,280 --> 00:40:24,620
Thank you for being my friend...

386
00:40:28,980 --> 00:40:32,900
It’s nothing you need to thank for…

387
00:40:32,900 --> 00:40:34,260
Right?

388
00:40:36,620 --> 00:40:38,260
Yeah...

389
00:40:39,760 --> 00:40:43,960
By the way, why do you
still have Kantaro’s?

390
00:40:43,960 --> 00:40:45,760
I never gave this back…

391
00:40:50,220 --> 00:40:53,460
- What’s that about?
- Sorry.

392
00:40:53,460 --> 00:40:55,760
You’ve always been like that.

393
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:58,060
Like cicada shells…

394
00:40:58,060 --> 00:41:02,720
That was you, Tabo.
I had snail shells.

395
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:04,220
Did you?

396
00:41:05,580 --> 00:41:10,440
Um... if you want, how about this?

397
00:41:12,740 --> 00:41:14,860
Moeka, unplug the second controller...

398
00:41:14,860 --> 00:41:16,260
Okay.

399
00:41:21,540 --> 00:41:23,280
Let’s do this!

400
00:41:24,360 --> 00:41:26,760
So I won’t forget everyone.

401
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:31,260
Yeah...

402
00:41:59,740 --> 00:42:03,240
Hey, hey, hey... whoa.

403
00:42:03,240 --> 00:42:06,320
Game over!
Chonmage wins.

404
00:42:06,320 --> 00:42:08,180
- I won...
- Not bad.

405
00:42:08,180 --> 00:42:09,760
Impressive.

406
00:42:09,760 --> 00:42:13,260
Master, three drinks from King...

407
00:42:13,260 --> 00:42:17,400
- No, four drinks for us!
- Okay, okay!

408
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:19,580
Then, bring the most
expensive one, please.

409
00:42:19,580 --> 00:42:22,260
- Hey!
- The loser should stay quiet.

410
00:42:24,580 --> 00:42:26,760
You’re good at this, Chonmage.

411
00:42:29,040 --> 00:42:31,280
- Let’s play again.
- Yeah.

412
00:42:34,260 --> 00:42:36,760
Have you seen Ms. Saruhashi?

413
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:38,260
Huh?

414
00:42:38,260 --> 00:42:42,260
Ah, she said she’s going
straight home from the interview.

415
00:42:42,260 --> 00:42:46,260
- Ah... I see...
- Yeah.

416
00:42:52,460 --> 00:42:54,820
- Huh?
- Um…

417
00:42:56,100 --> 00:42:58,760
She’s been pretty busy lately…

418
00:42:58,760 --> 00:43:01,040
Yeah, I guess.

419
00:43:01,040 --> 00:43:03,660
Well, she’s our star after all.

420
00:43:05,040 --> 00:43:08,260
Ah, maybe she got a
boyfriend or something?

421
00:43:10,960 --> 00:43:15,760
- Well, I’ll be going then.
- Okay, good work.

422
00:43:22,520 --> 00:43:26,680
“Sonoko Saruhashi’s choice”

423
00:43:51,440 --> 00:43:52,840
Sorry.

424
00:43:56,100 --> 00:43:57,480
Let’s continue.

425
00:43:58,320 --> 00:44:03,760
So, it all started at the reunion
held on October 12th.

426
00:44:05,760 --> 00:44:09,680
That night, Toshiki Takeda
died from a fall.

427
00:44:09,680 --> 00:44:13,520
After that, Emi Nakajima
died in an accident.

428
00:44:13,520 --> 00:44:17,120
And then Kanta Sakurai died in a fire.

429
00:44:17,120 --> 00:44:23,260
The first two were ruled accidents,
but Sakurai’s death was clearly a murder.

430
00:44:29,120 --> 00:44:30,760
That’s all.

431
00:44:36,100 --> 00:44:37,760
Thank you.

432
00:44:39,580 --> 00:44:43,760
No matter how you look at it,
this is a serial murder.
